1 (iii) the exercise by the Chairman of the Commission of the powers
2 granted under § 9–662 of this subtitle.
3 (b) (1) The Commission may regulate fees and other charges for medical
4 services or treatment under this subtitle.
5 (2) (I) THE COMMISSION SHALL REGULATE FEES AND OTHER
6 CHARGES FOR THE REIMBURSEMENT OF PRESCRIPTION DRUGS AND
7 PHARMACEUTICAL SERVICES UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
8 (II) REIMBURSEMENT UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS
9 PARAGRAPH SHALL BE LIMITED TO AN INDEX OR INDEXES BASED ON ACQUISITION
10 COST, CALCULATED ON A PER UNIT BASIS, AS OF THE DATE OF DISPENSING AND MAY
11 INCLUDE REASONABLE DISPENSING FEES.
12 (3) Each fee or other charge for medical service or treatment under this
13 subtitle is limited to the amount that prevails in the same community for similar treatment
14 of an injured individual with a standard of living that is comparable to that of the covered
15 employee.
16 [(3)] (4) At least once every 2 years, the Commission shall:
17 (i) review its guide of medical and surgical fees for completeness and
18 reasonableness; and
19 (ii) make appropriate revisions to the guide of medical and surgical
20 fees.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
22 October 1, 2025.

